Accept Decline 0 Your cart is empty Continue shopping Clear Close WR4AYC Repeater Group: Fostering Community and Public Service in Coral Springs Welcome, Ham Radio Enthusiasts! The WR4AYC Repeater Group is a friendly club based in Coral Springs, Florida, focused on public service, camaraderie, and all things ham radio. Who We Are: Established in 1993, we have a rich history of serving the Coral Springs community and beyond. Our diverse group of 22 members includes experienced hams and those new to the hobby. We share a passion for public service communication, ensuring vital connections during emergencies. Beyond public service, we explore various aspects of ham radio, including digital modes, VHF/UHF communication, and the technical aspects of maintaining our repeater. What We Do: Meetings: Join us on the 2nd Tuesday of every month at 7: 00 PM at Pizza Time Restaurant for informative discussions, project demonstrations, and of course, good company! Public Service: We are committed to supporting emergency response efforts and maintaining our repeater for reliable communication during critical situations. Learning and Sharing: Whether you're a seasoned ham or just starting out, we offer a supportive environment for learning new skills and sharing your knowledge with fellow enthusiasts. Why Join Us? Give back to your community: Be part of a group dedicated to public service and ensuring communication during emergencies. Expand your knowledge: Learn from experienced hams and explore various facets of ham radio technology and operation. Find camaraderie: Join a welcoming group of fellow enthusiasts who share your passion for ham radio. Ready to Get Involved? We encourage you to visit our website ( http://wr4ayc.org ) to learn more about our activities and upcoming meetings. Feel free to contact our President, Richard C. Clarke W4RCC, via email ( WR4AYC@arrl.net ) to ask questions or express your interest in joining the WR4AYC Repeater Group! We look forward to connecting with you! 73 (Best Regards) from the WR4AYC Repeater Group Share Share Reading next Solivita Radio Club: A Versatile Club with Something for Everyone Pensacola Amateur Radio Club (K4PNS): A Smaller Club with a Focus on Mentorship Leave a comment All comments are moderated before being published. Built-in 1922, the iconic landmark developed by Coral Gables founder and visionary George Merrick was the city’s first public building. In celebration of the Coral Gables Golf & Country Club’s centennial anniversary, the venue has been restored and reopened for the community and future generations to enjoy. ​ Each space at the Coral Gables Golf & Country Club is unique and features elements of history, luxury, and sophisticated elegance. The Club is offering new membership opportunities and private & corporate events. Our newly renovated 18-hole championship (par 71) course is in great shape and features the some of best greens in South Florida; fast, true, and smooth. The tee-to-green distances present a challenge to men, women and youth of all skill levels, ranging from a comfortable 5,331 on up to a challenging 6,779 yards from the tips. Our Course Superintendent is instrumental in maintaining the club's reputation for having the 'truest' greens in South Florida! Situated among the woods and waterways in one of the city's most distinctive residential neighborhoods, our course facilities include a secluded practice range, short game area, practice putting green and two course comfort stations. The Club is also one of only a few courses in the area which continues to extend walking privileges to the active community during 'off-peak' times at the discretion of the golf Pro Shop personnel. Come out and experience a relaxed golf atmosphere that you will truly enjoy.
